    kueche: "spanisch",
    zeit: 180,
    schwierigkeit: 'schwer',
    zutaten: ["3  EL Olivenöl", "1 small finely diced Zwiebel", "2 cloves chopped Knoblauch", "225g Tinned Tomatos", "1 EL Tomate", "2 TL Paprikapulver", "Prise Chilli Powder", "Prise Zucker", "Chopped Petersilie", "900g Kartoffeln", "2 EL Olivenöl"],
    zubereitung: ["step 1\r\nHeat the oil in a pan and fry the onion for about 5 mins until softened. Add the garlic, chopped tomatoes, tomato purée, sweet paprika, chilli powder, sugar and a pinch of salt, then bring to the boil, stirring occasionally. Lower to a simmer and cook for 10 mins until pulpy. Can be kept chilled for up to 24 hrs.", "step 2\r\nHeat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Pat the potatoes dry with kitchen paper, then tip into a roasting tin and toss in the olive oil and some seasoning. Roast for 40-50 mins until crisp and golden. Tip the potatoes into serving dishes and spoon over the tomato sauce. Sprinkle with some fresh parsley to serve."],
    image: 'images/recipes/patatas-bravas.jpg',
